Subject: [PATCH] flists: compile the AddrSync_18 override, not the deps copy

Repo:  tidelink  (git.soton.ac.uk / SoC-Labs mirror)
Apply: from the tidelink repo root:  git apply 0001-...patch
       (or:  patch -p1 < 0001-...patch)
File:  flists/tidelink_fpga.flist   (line 186)

WHY
---
tidelink_fpga.flist compiles TWO modules that disagree on a port list:

  * line 186  deps/.../wlink/WlinkGenericFCReplayAddrSync_18.v   -- NO obs_* ports
  * line 196  src/rtl/local_overrides/WlinkGenericFCReplayV2_13.v -- DRIVES obs_* ports

WlinkGenericFCReplayV2_13 (the local override) instantiates AddrSync_18 and wires
its obs_raddr / obs_mbx_* observation ports. The deps copy of AddrSync_18 does not
declare those ports (verified: `grep -c obs_ deps/.../WlinkGenericFCReplayAddrSync_18.v`
== 0), so as shipped the flist produces 7x Error-[UPIMI-E] (unknown port in module
instance).

Appending the override and leaning on VCS "last declaration wins" is NOT a fix: it
makes the netlist a property of the tool. VCS keeps the last; Verilator errors on a
duplicate module; some Xcelium/Icarus modes keep the FIRST -- i.e. the deps copy.
The deps copy LACKS the a2l ACK-ptr reset-skew fix (async-assert / sync-deassert of
w_reset into r_clk; see override lines 84-121). That bug is invisible to an idealised
single-clock sim (the override's own header, line 100-101, says so) and shows up on
silicon as the a2l 6-word / false-FULL wedge. A first-wins tool binding the deps copy
would ship that bug silently.

FIX
---
Swap the deps/ path on line 186 for the local_overrides/ path -- exactly what the
sibling flists already do:

  flists/tidelink_fpga_v2.flist:230    ${TIDELINK_HOME}/src/rtl/local_overrides/WlinkGenericFCReplayAddrSync_18.v
  flists/tidelink_a2l_replay_cdc.flist:44  ${TIDELINK_HOME}/src/rtl/local_overrides/WlinkGenericFCReplayAddrSync_18.v

AddrSync_18 is the ONLY AddrSync/FCReplay module with a local override that this
flist still pulls from deps/ (AddrSync{,_15,_3} have no override; V2_12/V2_13 already
point at local_overrides). After this change there is exactly one AddrSync_18 for
every tool, and flist/resolve_tidelink_flist.py in the nanosoc-ethernet-chiplet
superproject becomes a no-op that can be deleted (it prints a WARNING telling you so).

VERIFICATION
------------
  * grep confirms deps AddrSync_18 has 0 obs_ ports, override has 7.
  * The two sibling flists already carry the override path (cited above).
  * No other line in tidelink_fpga.flist references AddrSync_18.

--- a/flists/tidelink_fpga.flist
+++ b/flists/tidelink_fpga.flist
@@ -183,7 +183,7 @@
 ${TIDELINK_HOME}/src/rtl/local_overrides/WlinkGPIOPHY.v
 ${TIDELINK_HOME}/deps/axi-chiplet-controller/logical/wlink/WlinkGenericFCReplayAddrSync.v
 ${TIDELINK_HOME}/deps/axi-chiplet-controller/logical/wlink/WlinkGenericFCReplayAddrSync_15.v
-${TIDELINK_HOME}/deps/axi-chiplet-controller/logical/wlink/WlinkGenericFCReplayAddrSync_18.v
+${TIDELINK_HOME}/src/rtl/local_overrides/WlinkGenericFCReplayAddrSync_18.v
 ${TIDELINK_HOME}/deps/axi-chiplet-controller/logical/wlink/WlinkGenericFCReplayAddrSync_3.v
 ${TIDELINK_HOME}/deps/axi-chiplet-controller/logical/wlink/WlinkGenericFCReplayV2.v
 ${TIDELINK_HOME}/deps/axi-chiplet-controller/logical/wlink/WlinkGenericFCReplayV2_1.v
